
Heat template to setup a coreos cluster with everything
to support kubernetes.

based on corekube, which can instantiate on other infrastructures than openstack


What it does:
	1.   Make a NDS openstack data volume for this configuration
		docker create --name config-ostack-kube -v /nds/config/openstack nds-volume-base
	2.   Copy your openstack API rc file and the heat template in
		docker cp <your-rc-file> config-ostack-kube:/nds/config/openstack
		docker cp <heat-file.yaml> config-ostack-kube:/nds/config/openstack
	3.  Run the openstack cli container with your config
		docker run --name nds-ostack-deploy --volumes-from config-ostack-kube 
	4.  Uses openstack cli to find your ext-network name, external IP allocations, stuff.....
	5.  Instantiates the kubernetes stack
	6.  Instantiates services passwd in k8

What it doesn't:
	1.  Do any kind of tear-down.   This accomplished by hand using k8 cli.
	2.  Handle errors very well.....

